A trie is a tree for storing strings by shared prefixes.

- Each edge represents a character.
- Each node represents a prefix.
- A word is present if you can follow its characters from the root and end at a node marked as a complete word.

For lowercase English words:
- each node can have up to 26 children
- index `0` = `'a'`, `25` = `'z'`

### Why use a trie
Good for:
- fast word insert/search by characters
- prefix queries
- autocomplete-style problems

Typical complexities for word length `L`:
- `Insert`: `O(L)`
- `Search`: `O(L)`
- `StartsWith`: `O(L)`

Space can be higher than a hash set because many nodes are stored.

## C# implementation

Supports:
- `Insert(string word)`
- `Search(string word)`
- `StartsWith(string prefix)`

```csharp
public class Trie
{
    private class TrieNode
    {
        public TrieNode[] Children = new TrieNode[26];
        public bool IsWord;
    }

    private readonly TrieNode _root = new TrieNode();

    public void Insert(string word)
    {
        TrieNode current = _root;

        foreach (char c in word)
        {
            int index = c - 'a';
            if (current.Children[index] == null)
            {
                current.Children[index] = new TrieNode();
            }

            current = current.Children[index];
        }

        current.IsWord = true;
    }

    public bool Search(string word)
    {
        TrieNode node = FindNode(word);
        return node != null && node.IsWord;
    }

    public bool StartsWith(string prefix)
    {
        return FindNode(prefix) != null;
    }

    private TrieNode FindNode(string s)
    {
        TrieNode current = _root;

        foreach (char c in s)
        {
            int index = c - 'a';
            if (current.Children[index] == null)
            {
                return null;
            }

            current = current.Children[index];
        }

        return current;
    }
}
```

## Example

```csharp
Trie trie = new Trie();

trie.Insert("apple");

Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("apple"));    // true
Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("app"));      // false
Console.WriteLine(trie.StartsWith("app"));  // true

trie.Insert("app");
Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("app"));      // true
```

