A **monotonic queue** is a queue that keeps its elements in sorted order, usually **decreasing** for sliding-window maximums.

### Idea
For each new element:
- Remove smaller elements from the back, because they can never be the maximum again.
- Add the new element.
- Remove the front element if it falls out of the current window.
- The front always holds the maximum.

This makes each element enter and leave the queue at most once, so the total time is **O(n)**.

### JavaScript implementation

```js
function maxSlidingWindow(nums, k) {
  const deque = []; // stores indices
  const result = [];

  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    // Remove indices outside the current window
    if (deque.length && deque[0] <= i - k) {
      deque.shift();
    }

    // Remove smaller values from the back
    while (deque.length && nums[deque[deque.length - 1]] <= nums[i]) {
      deque.pop();
    }

    deque.push(i);

    // Start recording results once the first window is complete
    if (i >= k - 1) {
      result.push(nums[deque[0]]);
    }
  }

  return result;
}
```

### Example

